<p>Boys gathering snow in cups to melt it down for boiling purposes as the supply of water was extremely short &amp; we were on half rations. With the boisterous weather nothing could be landed on the beach. The Turks shelled us to-day and a number of our lads were wounded &amp; killed up on Lone Pine quarter.</p>
<p>Tuesday 30th Nov<br/>To-day the sun shone brightly &amp; the scene was lovely. The snow dazzled &amp; sparkled like diamonds under its feet. Of course by now most of it was hard &amp; frozen into icles. It was lovely to get the heatening of the rays of the sun.</p>
